medplum/medplum#7291.body:
Since we always include an upper bound on `lastUpdated` and generally a lower bound as well and always specify a less than range on `__version`:

```sql
select id, __version, deleted from "Patient" where deleted = false AND (__version < 2 OR __version is null) and "lastUpdated" < '2025-09-01' order by "lastUpdated" limit 50;

select id, __version, deleted from "Patient" where deleted = false AND (__version < 2 OR __version is null) and "lastUpdated" < '2025-09-01' AND "lastUpdated" > '2024-12-01' order by "lastUpdated" limit 50;
```

The ideal index would be some like the following:

```sql
create index "Patient_reindexing_idx" on "Patient" ("lastUpdated", __version) WHERE deleted = false;
```

This could likely replace the index on just `__version` and potentially the index on just `lastUpdated` as well, but that one would need more thought.

