medplum/medplum#7446.body:
Right now there are three test suites that intentionally use `flushdb` to get back to a clean cache state between tests. They are segregated by all other test suites by manually specifying `config.redis.db = 6` while the default test config uses `config.redis.db = 7`. This generally work well enough, but due to a subtle configuration bug, one of those test files was unintentionally flushing db 7 instead of 6.

A more maintainable alternative could be using an alternative to `flushdb` like the following. It would work well with the `config.redis.keyPrefix` provided by `ioredis`.

```
// Instead of: await getRedis().flushdb()
// Use pattern-based deletion:
const redis = getRedis();
const keys = await redis.keys('test-specific-prefix:*');
if (keys.length > 0) {
  await redis.del(...keys);
}
```

medplum/medplum#7468.body:
### Overview

In, the `$set-accounts ` operation, the target resource is updated using repo instead of systemRepo. See [this line](https://github.com/medplum/medplum/blob/e43c875df23cd562374c2bd6325a31885dbf30cf/packages/server/src/fhir/operations/set-accounts.ts#L144).

This means that there is different behavior depending on whether or not you pass the `x-medplum : extended` header. 

### Example scenario - removing a reference from Patient's compartment

1. Create a Patient
2. Now call `$set-accounts` with 
```
{
    "resourceType": "Parameters",
    "parameter": [
        {
            "name": "accounts",
            "valueReference": {
                "reference": "Organization/123"
            }
        },
 {
            "name": "accounts",
            "valueReference": {
                "reference": "Organization/456"
            }
        },
        {
            "name": "propagate",
            "valueBoolean": false
        }
    ]
}
```
3. Now that `meta.accounts` is populated on the Patient, there is different behavior depending on whether or not `x-medplum : extended` is added on the next `$set-accounts` call:


call `$set-accounts` with to remove the first Organization reference
```
{
    "resourceType": "Parameters",
    "parameter": [
      {
            "name": "accounts",
            "valueReference": {
                "reference": "Organization/456"
            }
        },
        {
            "name": "propagate",
            "valueBoolean": false
        }
    ]
}
```

Observed behavior without `x-medplum : extended` - no updates are made to the Patient

Observed behavior with `x-medplum : extended` - the Organization reference is removed [Intended behavior]


### Fix

The update to the target resource should be called with systemRepo, after applying the appropriate permission check for write access to that resource type

