`Crawler.crawlPropertyValue` and `AsyncCrawler.crawlPropertyValue` do not properly load types defined in resource profiles when invoking `getDataType`. Two approaches that work; unsure which would be the better fix; but option 2 feels more correct since it doesn't depend on `loadDataType` having been called and instead uses the profile `schema` directly.

### Option 1
```typescript
private crawlPropertyValue(value: TypedValueWithPath, path: string, schema: InternalTypeSchema): void {
  if (!isPrimitiveType(value.type)) {
    // Requires having called `loadDataType(profile);` before the crawler is used, e.g. in Repository.validateProfiles()
    const type = getDataType(value.type, schema.url). 
  }
}
```

### Option 2
```typescript
private crawlPropertyValue(value: TypedValueWithPath, path: string, schema: InternalTypeSchema): void {
  if (!isPrimitiveType(value.type)) {
    const type = schema.innerTypes?.find((t) => t.name === value.type) ?? getDataType(value.type);
  }
}
```

The `Invalid patient with US Core Patient profile (communication.language not in ValueSet)` test in `src/fhir/repo.test.ts` demonstrates the currently incorrect behavior.

