medplum/medplum#8639.body:
  In ValueSetAutocomplete.tsx, the count parameter passed to
  medplum.valueSetExpand() is hardcoded to 10. This should be configurable with
  a default of 10.

https://medplum.slack.com/archives/C0A2DPWBMV5/p1773248040778719

  Current Behavior

  // packages/react/src/ValueSetAutocomplete/ValueSetAutocomplete.tsx:68-76
  const valueSet = await medplum.valueSetExpand(
    {
      ...expandParams,
      url: binding,
      filter: input,
      count: 10,  // hardcoded
    },
    { signal }
  );

  expandParams is already accepted as a prop (Partial<ValueSetExpandParams>),
  but because count: 10 comes after the spread, any count value passed via
  expandParams is always overridden.
